              "body": "![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)\n\nIf `hooks/inject` (bash) and the TypeScript CLI share the same log files, they must use a compatible locking mechanism to ensure safe log rotation. Relying on atomic appends for small lines is insufficient when one process (the CLI) is renaming the file for rotation while another (the hook) is opening it for append. The bash implementation should use a lock compatible with the one in `src/lib/lockfile.ts`.\n\n```suggestion\n  - keep log line size bounded; acquire `withLogLock` equivalent (must be compatible with the TS implementation in `src/lib/lockfile.ts` to support safe rotation)\n```",
