                "login": "chatgpt-codex-connector"
              },
              "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Align retrieval output contract with envelope format**\n\nR4 says `cairn recall/get/list-topics` \"return markdown to stdout,\" but R8 in the same document requires those retrieval responses to be a length-prefixed JSON envelope. This leaves two incompatible wire contracts for the same commands, so downstream callers and future tests can implement different assumptions and break interoperability. Please make R4 explicitly match the envelope contract (or remove the envelope requirement) so there is a single output format.\n\nUseful? React with 👍 / 👎.",
