          "nodes": [
            {
              "id": "PRRC_kwDOSDaMq866P1v-",
              "author": {
                "login": "copilot-pull-request-reviewer"
              },
              "body": "Unit 5 proposes creating `.claude/settings.json`, but this repo currently has no `.claude/` directory and plugin metadata lives under `.claude-plugin/`. To avoid future implementation drift, consider clarifying where deny rules should actually live in this project (repo-tracked vs installer-generated vs user `~/.claude`), and adjust the file paths in this plan accordingly.\n```suggestion\n**Dependencies:** Requires a concrete install story that distinguishes repo-tracked plugin metadata from generated/user-local Claude settings. In this repo, defaults/templates should live under `.claude-plugin/`; any resulting project-local `.claude/settings.json` or user `~/.claude/...` config should be treated as installer-generated or user-managed, not committed here.\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `.claude-plugin/` metadata/template(s) for deny patterns covering `raw/`, `sessions/`, and `.cairn/*.jsonl` logs per R13a; document how installation materializes those rules into the effective Claude settings location if needed\n- Create: `.claude-plugin/hooks/security-self-test` (or similar) and register it in repo-tracked `.claude-plugin` hook metadata (for any installer to materialize into host-specific hook configuration as needed) as a manually invokable hook and/or a script that `doctor` can reference\n- Modify: `src/commands/doctor.ts` (warn-first: prints “run security self-test” guidance; does not pretend it can simulate tool denies)\n- Test: `tests/security-self-test.test.ts` (limited: asserts script output contract and sentinel creation; the actual tool deny behavior is host-dependent)\n\n**Approach:**\n- Enforcement config:\n  - define repo-tracked deny-rule defaults under `.claude-plugin/`, not by committing `.claude/settings.json` directly in this repository\n  - parameterize deny patterns to match the resolved vault path(s) as best as the host permits when installed/generated\n  - preserve any existing downstream deny rules if present in generated/user config (e.g. `.entire/metadata/**`)\n  - document the precedence/merge story explicitly: repo template/defaults vs installer-generated project config vs user `~/.claude` overrides\n```",
