              },
              "body": "This section says “Verified: the plugin already uses this pattern for `.entire/metadata/**` in `.claude/settings.json`”, but the repository doesn’t contain a `.claude/settings.json` (or any other tracked deny config). Either link to the real existing deny configuration file (if it’s generated/packaged elsewhere) or downgrade this to an assumption and keep the verification item open.\n```suggestion\n- Claude Code `permissions.deny` with path-scoped `Read(...)` entries is assumed to be a workable enforcement mechanism for this design, but the existing plugin use of this pattern for `.entire/metadata/**` has not yet been verified in a tracked repository config file. **Keep this verification open during planning unless a generated or packaged deny config can be linked explicitly.**\n- Whether `.claude/settings.json` in the plugin directory applies to agents running in any project that has the plugin loaded remains unverified. If path-scoping needs to change (e.g. the vault is outside the project), the deny rule needs to cover both the default `~/cairn` and `.cairn`-resolved paths. **Flagged as needs verification during planning.**\n```",
